Former deputy Finance Minister Mcebisi Jonas has joined telecommunications giant MTN’s board as a non-executive director. The MTN Group announced on Monday that Jonas will join the board along with businesswoman Bajabulile Swazi Tshabalala. Jonas was fired as deputy Minister by then President Jacob Zuma along with former Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan in 2017. Jonas currently serves alongside four investment envoys appointed by President Cyril Ramaphosa to reel in investors to South Africa. Last month, Ramaphosa appointed Jonas,  former Finance Minister Trevor Manuel, Chairman of Liberty Group and former CEO of Standard Bank Jacko Maree and Phumzile Langeni Executive Chairperson of Afropulse Group as team of business and finance experts tasked with venturing into the world to seek investment for the country. -Afro Reporter 